{"word":"ἀπραξία","slug":"ἀπραξία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπραξία</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄπρακτος'><el>ἄπρακτος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a not acting, inaction</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>rest from business</i>, in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>holidays</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>want of success</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}